title.narrative: IMMUNISATION SERVICES

description.narrative: The most vulnerable children and women access a minimum social protection package, which contributes to Child Health, Health And Emergencies, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most vulnerable children and women access a minimum social protection package

title.narrative: The most vulnerable children and women access a minimum social protection package

description.narrative: Routine immunization coverage remained low as 34% for pentavalent 3 and 36% for measles despite efforts to re-establish the cold chain system; 31 solar fridges were installed. Supplementary campaigns such as tetanus, meningitis A, polio and measles were conducted, and RRM remained a powerful modality to reach children unserved otherwise. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2015
